result.execSummary:
The defendant Daniel Gane Findley was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Failure to Support Child (120 Days+), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes: Defendant shall pay all court obligations and supervision fees.
Defendant shall not use any drug without a valid prescription from his doctor.
Defendant shall pay court ordered child support obligations from prison wages.

Defendant shall submit 5 job applications per week until employment is secured.
Defendant shall participate in any treatment deemed necessary by DOC.
Defendant shall submit DNA sample, if not already attained.
Payment of court obligations is limited to 25% of prison wages.
